narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Each student does a 15-minute presentation once a year. I gained practice presenting my research and answering questions about my project.
I learned about what kind of research projects my peers and other grad students are involved in.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It helps you improve your presentations in some way. The participation is not very high.

The sessions are much too long and people really stop paying attention after the first few presentations. The second year lightning talks also seem like a waste of time because they are not long enough for the presenter to actually describe their project. We also don't receive very meaningful feedback (none from the instructors, and the quality of the feedback from other students varies). It doesn't seem like the goal of the class is to help us improve our presentation skills. It seems more like this is just a requirement that we all have to do, but no one actually cares about it.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: No, but it is a requirement.
Yes, you will find diverse research topics in the seminar.
